## Failure modes

| What can go wrong | How mtix behaves | What you do |
|---|---|---|
| **Hub unreachable** during push | `mtix sync push` errors with a redacted message; `meta.sync.consecutive_errors` bumps. In MTIX_SYNC_HOOK=1 mode (pre-push hook) it warns and skips. | Retry once connectivity is back. The local queue is durable. |
| **Hub unreachable** during pull | Same — error + bumped counter. Daemon catches up on the next tick. | No action needed if you're not blocked. |
| **Hub unreachable consecutive ≥ 3** | `mtix_sync_workflow` MCP tool reports `hub-unreachable` and recommends `mtix sync doctor`. | Run `mtix sync doctor`; verify TLS / DSN / connectivity. |
| **Local queue full** (`sync.max_queue_size` cap reached) | Next emit returns `ErrSyncQueueFull` with a remediation message. Event is NOT silently dropped. | Run `mtix sync push --force`, or raise the cap. |
| **Hook bypassed** (`git push --no-verify`) | Local queue retains pending events; hub stays at the older state until next push. | If freshness matters, graduate to the safety-critical workflow's server-side enforcement OR run the daemon. |
| **Schema mismatch** (developer running an older mtix binary) | `mtix sync init` / `clone` refuses with a structured error mentioning the schema version. | Upgrade the local binary (`go install github.com/hyper-swe/mtix/cmd/mtix@latest`). |
| **Divergent history** (you initialized a hub but a teammate already initialized one with the same project prefix) | `mtix sync init` refuses with `ErrSyncDivergentHistory`. | Either join the existing hub via `mtix sync clone`, or run `mtix sync reconcile --import-as PARENT-ID` to graft your local nodes under a new parent. |
| **Wrong sslmode** in DSN (e.g. `sslmode=disable`) | mtix refuses to connect unless `--insecure-tls` is set AND host is loopback. | Fix the DSN to `sslmode=verify-full`. |
| **DSN in a tracked file** | mtix refuses to load DSN from any tracked config; fail-closed at `Source()`. | Move it to `MTIX_SYNC_DSN` env var or `.mtix/secrets` (mode 0600). |
| **Lost laptop with un-pushed events** | The local pending queue dies with the machine; hub never saw those events. | See "Disaster recovery" below — explicit procedure. Recovery is to clone from hub onto a fresh machine. |

